# CSS conventions

Class registry and block names: [docs/ui-elements.md](../../docs/ui-elements.md). **Palette tokens:** [docs/ui-palette.md](../../docs/ui-palette.md) (read before any UI change). Template/button rules: [contraponto-ui.mdc](contraponto-ui.mdc). HTMX behavior: [docs/htmx-events.md](../../docs/htmx-events.md).

## Stylesheet bundles

| File | Scope |
|------|--------|
| `style/fonts.css` | `@font-face` only — no layout or components |
| `style/main.css` | `:root` tokens, reset, shell, public reading, shared primitives (`.btn`, `.form-group`, `.container`, HTMX feedback) |
| `style/manage.css` | Logged-in operations (library, dashboard, CRUD, review, notifications) |
| `style/write.css` | Write editor (`/write`, `/write/draft/*`) only |

Load order in [components/head.html](../../src/main/resources/templates/components/head.html): fonts → main → manage → write → third-party.

- Put new rules in the bundle that owns the primary surface; extend primitives in **main.css** instead of duplicating `.btn` / `.form-group`.
- **Never** edit `style/third-party/`. No Sass/Less/PostCSS build step.

## Design tokens

- Colors, spacing, typography, radius, shadows, motion: `var(--…)` from `:root` in **main.css** (`--color-primary`, `--spacing-md`, `--font-sans`, `--duration-normal`, `--htmx-opacity-busy`, …).
- Add new global tokens only in `main.css` `:root` blocks; reference them elsewhere.
- **Do not** introduce new hard-coded hex colors in main/manage (existing debt in `write.css` — use tokens when touching that file).

## Naming and selectors

- **BEM:** `block`, `block__element`, `block--modifier`; utilities `u-*` (e.g. `u-hidden`, `u-mt-md`).
- **kebab-case** only; page blocks match domain pages (`library-page`, `article-card`, `notifications-page`).
- Prefer single-class or shallow compounds (`.btn.btn--primary`); avoid deep descendant chains and IDs in CSS.
- State for HTMX: use shipped classes (`.htmx-request`, `.htmx-indicator`) — styles live in **main.css** only.

## File style

- **2-space** indent (match `main.css` / `manage.css`).
- Section banners: `/* ========== SECTION NAME ========== */` before each major block.
- One declaration per line; properties roughly grouped (layout → box → typography → visual → motion).
- Transitions: `var(--duration-normal)` and `var(--ease-out)` where possible.
- Responsive: **mobile-first** — base styles target the smallest viewport; add layout enhancements with `@media (min-width: …)` using breakpoints from [ui-palette.md](../../docs/ui-palette.md) (`--bp-sm` 480px, `--bp-md` 768px, `--bp-lg` 1024px, `--bp-xl` 1280px). Use `@media (max-width: …)` only for rare removals during migration (e.g. hiding labels until there is room).
- `!important` only for utilities (`[hidden]`, `.u-hidden`) or reduced-motion overrides — not for component tweaks.

## Templates vs CSS

- Layout and look: **classes in CSS**, not inline `style="…"` in Qute (exceptions: email HTML under `templates/email/`, dynamic chart bar heights in analytics).
- Prefer server-rendered structure + HTMX swaps over JS-driven styling ([contraponto-javascript.mdc](contraponto-javascript.mdc)).

## New UI checklist

0. Read [ui-palette.md](../../docs/ui-palette.md); use existing tokens or extend `:root` + the doc together.
1. Register the block in [ui-elements.md](../../docs/ui-elements.md).
2. Add CSS to the correct bundle with tokens + BEM.
3. Use existing `.btn` modifiers — never `btn--sm` (use `btn--small`).
4. Update [ui-guidelines.md](../../docs/ui-guidelines.md) when adding a new page type.
